        <p>Flat roofs are common on Bronx homes, apartment buildings, storefronts, and commercial properties. When a flat roof starts leaking, the problem may come from damaged roofing material, separated seams, loose flashing, clogged drains, roof edges, parapet walls, or roof penetrations such as vents and pipes.</p>
        <p>This Bronx page is focused on flat roof repair first. Structural waterproofing, TPO, EPDM, metal roofing, torch down, and modified bitumen are included because they are often part of solving the same leak or water-intrusion problem.</p>
        <p>Maximum Roofing helps Bronx property owners identify the source of the problem and choose the right repair method for the roofing system on the building. Our goal is simple: stop the leak, protect the structure, waterproof vulnerable areas, and explain the repair clearly before work begins.</p>

