        <h2>TPO, EPDM, Metal, Torch Down &amp; Modified Bitumen Roofing in the Bronx</h2>
        <p>Bronx buildings can use different roofing systems depending on the structure, slope, drainage, and use of the property. Maximum Roofing works with common flat and low-slope systems including TPO roofing, EPDM roofing, torch down roofing, modified bitumen roofing, and metal roofing.</p>
        <p>Torch down and modified bitumen are common choices for flat and low-slope roofs. TPO is often used on commercial flat roofs because it is a single-ply roofing system. EPDM is a rubber roofing system used on many low-slope roofs. Metal roofing can appear on commercial buildings, additions, canopies, and sloped roof sections.</p>
        <p>Maximum Roofing can inspect the existing roof system and explain whether a repair, patch, waterproofing detail, maintenance service, coating, or replacement is the better option for the building.</p>
